{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "31d85b43-3080-451f-aebd-4ffd89f9bc36",
    "name": "backend_pomodoro_task",
    "description": "Collection para validar contratos e rotas públicas do backend Pomodoro.\n\nPré-requisitos:\n- importar também o environment `backend_pomodoro_task.postman_environment.json`;\n- preencher `api_key`;\n- ajustar `base_url` conforme o ambiente.\n\nFluxo recomendado:\n1. Health\n2. Groups > List\n3. Activities > List by Group\n4. Activities > Next\n5. Activities > Start Current\n6. Activities > Active\n7. Activities > Status Current\n8. Activities > Complete Current\n9. Queue > Skip Current\n10. History\n\nA collection tenta propagar automaticamente `group_id`, `activity_id`, `queue_item_id`, `queue_id`, `schedule_id` e `execution_id` entre as chamadas.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "const required = ['base_url', 'api_key'];",
          "const missing = required.filter((key) => !pm.environment.get(key));",
          "if (missing.length) {",
          "  console.warn('Postman environment missing:', missing.join(', '));",
          "}",
          "const normalizeNumeric = (key) => {",
          "  const value = pm.environment.get(key);",
          "  if (value === undefined || value === null || value === '') return;",
          "  const numeric = String(value).trim();",
          "  if (/^\\d+$/.test(numeric)) {",
          "    pm.environment.set(key, numeric);",
          "  }",
          "};",
          "['group_id', 'activity_id', 'queue_id', 'queue_item_id', 'schedule_id', 'execution_id', 'category_id', 'created_activity_id'].forEach(normalizeNumeric);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "json_headers",
      "value": "application/json"
    }
  ],
